5:
Oof, we're running low on funds. 
We'll be eating plain curry for a while 
if this keeps up.
12: Haven't you ever learned to knock?!
17:
It's somewhere on my to-do list. 
More importantly, what's this talk about 
plain curry?!
26:
I see... 
Are you keeping a budget?
33:
This won't do, Alk! 
You need to keep track of all variable 
expenses, especially with an 
inconsistent cash flow.
39:
Don't look at me like that! 
These are basic budgeting 
fundamentals!
43:
Let's have a look-see at your expenses. 
Beef jerky, fish, eggs, bread, 
vegetables...
48:
Someone on this crew's been eating 
too much. 
It's no wonder we're out of money.
55:
Not only that, you're spending 
exorbitant amounts on lavish 
ingredients, booze, and more booze!
57: This... is all from me and my crew, isn't it?
68:
I guess the pirates could just live off 
bread and water for a while...
72:
No, no, no! There's no way in hell 
I'd ever leave my crew high and dry!
76:
Then go fishing for once or something! 
You're supposed to be pirates, aren't 
you?
79:
Hmm, yes... 
Hold on just a minute. What's that?
82:
Huh? This? 
It's just a pamphlet I got from the 
Palpebra guild.
87:
Lemme see that! 
Yes, yes... Here's the answer to our 
problems—adventurer subsidies!
94:
You should know at least this much 
if you're going to take on quests! 
Anything you purchase for a quest 
counts as a deductible.
97:
Basically, you'll get some of your 
money back!
102:
Whoa, no way! 
What is this sorcery?!
106:
Heh-heh... 
Just leave your financial troubles to 
Mamiya Marina!
110:
Oookay... I think that should do it! 
Quite a total, if I do say so myself.
113:
I'm impressed how you can drink while 
doing paperwork...
117:
You've got it all wrong—
I can't do this without having a drink 
first!
120:
All these numbers just remind me of 
my stupid boss's face from back in the 
day.
124:
You mean from your original world, 
Marina?
128:
Yep... It was a pretty dull place, but 
looking back, at least it was peaceful.
131: Do you want to go back someday?
134:
Hmm... That's a toughie. 
I guess I'd go back when it feels right, 
you know?
141:
I'm Marina the Crimson Blade, 
remember? If I want something, 
I get it!
143:
But I don't think I'm ready to go back 
just yet. 
My journey's not over yet, 
and neither is yours, right?
146:
I guess I could make do with instant 
noodles now and then, but you're 
cooking's just too good, Alk!
149:
Way to start buttering me up out of 
nowhere...
153:
I mean it! 
I've traversed countless seas, 
but your cooking TOTALLY is out of this 
world!
155: It's so good I could just marry you!
158:
Marina... 
You've had too much to drink, haven't 
you?
163:
Ehehe... I'm fiiine, Alk! 
And so are you and Stella! 
You're all fiiiine!
166:
I'm the Crimson Blade, 
remember?! I'll marry the both of 
you if I want! It'd be... a HUGE 
party...
173:
Welp... 
I guess she's staying here tonight.
175:
*sigh* Even in this state, she really is 
beautiful, huh?
